{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ca02ac3a-e423-43e9-ac60-cbe50e9f0d6e","content":"Run **`dotnet workload update`**. After a SDK update, your installed workloads (e.g., `maui`) need to be updated to versions compatible with the new SDK. This command downloads and installs the latest workload versions that match your current SDK.\n\n**`dotnet workload repair`** is for fixing corrupted or incomplete installations — it reinstalls the *same* workload versions without upgrading them, so it won't resolve a version mismatch caused by a SDK update.\n\n**Quick fix:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload update\ndotnet build\n```\n\nIf you still see issues after updating, run `dotnet workload list` to confirm the `maui` workload is installed and its version aligns with your SDK.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d116ffe7-e111-4b4f-8a36-70685327da41","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI workload management — specifically whether to use `dotnet workload update` or `dotnet workload repair` after a SDK update broke their build.\n\nThis is a general knowledge question, not tied to any code in the current directory. I can answer from my knowledge of .NET tooling.\n\n**`dotnet workload update`** — Downloads and installs the latest available versions of all installed workloads. Use this when you want to bring workloads up to the newest release.\n\n**`dotnet workload repair`** — Reinstalls all installed workloads to ensure they match the current SDK version. It doesn't upgrade them to newer versions; it just fixes the installation to be consistent with the SDK you have.\n \nWhen a .NET SDK update breaks the build, it's usually because the workloads are out of sync with the new SDK version. In this case, `dotnet workload update` is the right move — it'll bring all your workloads like MAUI up to versions that work with your current SDK, whereas `dotnet workload repair` is really just for fixing corrupted installations.","outputTokens":461,"requestId":"F409:1497BC:1EAAA67:2274DE0:69E81955"},"id":"c8492f21-fc04-4493-8325-75d2708f71fd","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:42:08.567Z","parentId":"d14034b8-9a24-44fe-a0ec-d1d1a2378a22"}
